Package: bridgr
Type: Package
Title: Bridging Data Frequencies for Timely Economic Forecasts
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("Marc", "Burri", ,"marc.burri91@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8974-9090"))
  )
Maintainer: Marc Burri <marc.burri91@gmail.com>
Description: Implements bridge models for nowcasting and forecasting macroeconomic variables by linking higher-frequency indicator variables to a lower-frequency target series. The package standardizes input data, infers regular frequencies, forecasts missing indicator observations, and aggregates indicators to the target frequency before fitting a regression with autoregressive target dynamics. Frequency alignment can be customized through user-supplied conversion rules. For more on bridge models, see Baffigi, A., Golinelli, R., & Parigi, G. (2004) <doi:10.1016/S0169-2070(03)00067-0>, Burri (2023) <https://www5.unine.ch/RePEc/ftp/irn/pdfs/WP23-02.pdf> or Schumacher (2016) <doi:10.1016/j.ijforecast.2015.07.004>.
